Project Benefits

Measurable Impact for
Santa Rosa

This budget-neutral program delivers quantifiable improvements across financial, environmental, and operational dimensions—avoiding capital expenses through guaranteed energy savings, utility incentives, grant funds, and low-interest financing.

Climate Resilience

Microgrids and battery storage ensure continuous operation of essential city services during PSPS events and grid disruptions.

72hrs backup power

Budget-Neutral Savings

Self-funded through guaranteed savings, utility incentives, grant funds, and low-interest financing—leveraging federal ITC incentives from the Inflation Reduction Act.

$4.2Mlifecycle savings

Carbon Reduction

Significant reduction in municipal greenhouse gas emissions through facility electrification, solar generation, and operational efficiency gains.

2,400metric tons CO₂/yr

Fleet Electrification

Expanded EV charging infrastructure supports the City’s transition to zero-emission vehicles and promotes community adoption.

48EV chargers deployed

Facility Electrification

Shifting HVAC and major equipment from fossil fuels to electric power to control costs and reduce greenhouse gas emissions across municipal facilities.

22facilities upgraded

Public Safety Lighting

City-wide smart LED conversion improves nighttime visibility, reduces light pollution, and enhances community safety through networked controls.

12,000+LED fixtures installed
Project Scope

Comprehensive Infrastructure Upgrade

Refined through rigorous engineering analysis, targeting high-impact improvements across municipal facilities.

01

Energy Resilience & Microgrids

Deployment of battery energy storage and solar PV systems for reliable backup during grid disruptions and PSPS events.

02

Critical Infrastructure Hardening

Modernization of HVAC and electrical systems at key facilities to ensure continuous essential city services during emergencies.

03

Facility Electrification

Shifting HVAC and other major equipment to be powered by electricity rather than fossil fuels to control costs and reduce greenhouse gas emissions.

04

Smart LED Lighting & Controls

City-wide conversion to networked LED lighting to improve visibility, reduce light pollution, and lower energy costs.

05

Fleet Electrification Infrastructure

Expansion of EV charging stations to support zero-emission fleet transition and promote public adoption.

06

Operational Efficiency

Building automation upgrades to optimize energy performance and reduce long-term maintenance burdens.
